<h3 id="represenation">Represenation</h3>

<h4 id="array-representaion">Array Representaion</h4>
<ol>
  <li>if a Node is at index $i$</li>
  <li>its left child is at $2*i$</li>
  <li>its left child is at $2*i+1$</li>
  <li>its parent is at $i/2$</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="linked-list-presentation">Linked list presentation</h4>
<ol>
  <li>we can based on the position relationship between parent and child, to create
a tree.</li>
</ol>

<h3 id="tree">Tree</h3>

<h4 id="complete-binary-tree">Complete Binary Tree</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Represented by array, no blank space in the array.</li>
</ol>

<h4 id="galois">Galois</h4>
<ol>
  <li>Every data structure can be representation by two methods, array or linked
list.</li>
</ol>
